OL,3,CCould Labour's workers' rights
OL,4,Clegislation be diluted after Rayner's
OL,5,Cdeparture?
OL,7,FThe government call the plans the
OL,8,F"biggest upgrade to workers' rights in
OL,9,Fa generation", but business groups,
OL,10,Falong with the Conservatives, have
OL,11,Fwarned the Employment Rights Bill
OL,12,Fcould stifle growth.
OL,14,FFormer Deputy Prime Minister Angela
OL,15,FRayner was seen as a champion of
OL,16,Fworkers' rights before she left
OL,17,Fgovernment on Friday after failing to
OL,18,Fpay #40,000 in stamp duty on a flat in
OL,19,FHove.
OL,21,FWhat's in the Employment Rights Bill?
