OL,3,CCould Labour's workers' rights
OL,4,Clegislation be diluted after Rayner's
OL,5,Cdeparture?
OL,7,FSpeaking to ITV News on Monday, Shadow
OL,8,FBusiness Secretary Andrew Griffith
OL,9,Fcalled the bill "330 pages of red tape
OL,10,Fthat will grind the economy to a halt."
OL,12,FWhy are unions concerned?
OL,14,FThe departure of Angela Rayner from
OL,15,Fgovernment also triggered a broader
OL,16,Fcabinet reshuffle - that saw Business
OL,17,FSecretary Jonathan Reynolds moved to
OL,18,Fthe role of chief whip, and Employment
OL,19,FMinister Justin Madders sacked. All
OL,20,Fthree were seen as champions of the
OL,21,Fworker's rights plans.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
